"title": "5230: beggars",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5230",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>People in great need who appeal for help, both from others and from God.</p>\n<h2>Appeals for material help</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:26\">2KI 6:26</a></strong> <em>During a time of famine</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:3\">LUK 16:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:3-2Kgs8:5\">2KI 8:3–8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:16\">JOB 19:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:4-Job24:5\">JOB 24:4–24:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:11-Job29:12\">JOB 29:11–29:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25\">PSA 37:25</a> <em>never having to beg seen as God's blessing</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:10\">PSA 109:10</a> <em>begging seen as God's judgment</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:4\">LAM 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Appeals for mercy from others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:3\">EST 8:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:25\">1SA 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:4\">2SA 14:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:13\">2KI 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:8\">EST 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:7\">EST 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:28\">JOB 30:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:26-Matt18:32\">MAT 18:26–18:32</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of beggars</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:46\">MRK 10:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35\">LUK 18:35</a> <em>blind Bartimaeus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:20-Luke16:21\">LUK 16:20–16:21</a> <em>Lazarus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:8\">JHN 9:8</a> <em>the man born blind</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:2-Acts3:3\">ACT 3:2–3:3</a> <em>the crippled man at the temple gate</em></p>\n<h2>Care for the destitute commended</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:6–58:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:11\">MAT 26:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:7\">MRK 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:8\">JHN 12:8</a> <em>Jesus Christ implies that we should care for them.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:11\">DEU 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:17\">PRO 19:17</a> <em>kindness to the poor rewarded</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:13\">PRO 21:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:9\">PRO 22:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:27\">PRO 28:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:9\">PRO 31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:20\">PRO 31:20</a> <em>the behaviour of the wife of noble character</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:10\">ZEC 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:42\">MAT 5:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:30\">LUK 6:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ and the rich young man</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:33\">LUK 12:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:13\">LUK 14:13</a></p>\n<h2>Pleas for God's help</h2>\n<h3>From the Israelites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23\">EXO 2:23</a></strong> <em>In the OT there are many examples of the Israelites begging God for his help in times of dire need.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:7\">JOS 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:3\">JDG 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:6\">JDG 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:11\">2CH 14:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:5\">AMO 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>From individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:6\">PSA 18:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:2\">PSA 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:2\">JON 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:2\">HAB 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:27\">LUK 16:27</a></p>\n<h2>People begged Jesus Christ for help</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:35-Matt14:36\">MAT 14:35–14:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:56\">MRK 6:56</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:31\">MAT 8:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:12\">MRK 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:32\">LUK 8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:26\">MRK 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:32\">MRK 7:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:47\">MRK 10:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12\">LUK 5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40\">MRK 1:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:28\">LUK 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:38-Luke9:40\">LUK 9:38–9:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:47\">JHN 4:47</a></p>",
